[
  "Kenneth Lo founded clothing manufacturer Crystal Group with his wife in 1970. ",
  "He built a modest sweater factory into one of Asia's largest garment manufacturers, with 68,000 employees at 20 sites around the world. ",
  "Crystal's customers include Fast Retailing, Gap, Abercrombie & Fitch, Nike, Adidas and Puma. ",
  "Lo, whose fortune includes that of his wife and his son Andrew, is chairman of the group while Andrew is chief executive. ",
  "He is the eldest son of the late textile magnate Law Ting-pong. His brother is fellow billionaire Law Kar Po."
]